  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "Minimal Repro:\r\n- Create 2 different disks\r\n- Create 2 Pods each using one of the disks\r\n- Start both pods on the same node\r\n\r\nYou will notice **one** of the disks gets `NodeStageVolume`ed to a path: `/var/lib/kubelet/plugins/kubernetes.io/csi/pv/mypvc/globalmount`, then **both** disks are `NodePublishVolume`ed from `/var/lib/kubelet/plugins/kubernetes.io/csi/pv/mypvc/globalmount` to a target path: `/var/lib/kubelet/pods/{POD_UUID}/volumes/kubernetes.io~csi/mypvc/mount` which is similar but at least uses the pod `UUID`.\r\n\r\nBoth of these volumes are being treated as the same volume in the Kubelet even though they are definitely not the same volume. Note: it may not be \"treated\" as the same volume - it may just be that since the paths are the same the following volumes see that the path is already a mountpoint and skip the `NodeStage` step. This is the more likely scenario based on observations.\r\n\r\nThe `mypvc` value is the \"name\" of the inline-volume. These can obviously be the same across different pods - we should actually be placing it in a more unique directory (based off the translated `volumeHandle` maybe?).\r\n\r\n/cc @ddebroy @msau42 @jsafrane @misterikkit @leakingtapan ",
